Pre-fill onboarding fields from ENS profile data. **Only fill empty fields** — never overwrite user-edited data.

```typescript
useEffect(() => {
  if (ensProfile && !initialData) {
    // Only pre-fill if no existing profile data
    setData(prev => ({
      ...prev,
      fullName: prev.fullName || ensProfile.name || "",
      oneLineIntro: prev.oneLineIntro || ensProfile.description || "",
      website: prev.website || ensProfile.url || "",
      // photo handled separately in 2D-5
    }))
  }
}, [ensProfile])
```

**Mapping (ENS → Onboarding):**
| ENS Record | Onboarding Field | Condition |
|-----------|-----------------|-----------|
| name | fullName | Only if empty |
| description | oneLineIntro | Only if empty |
| url | website (websiteUrl) | Only if empty |
| avatar | photo slot | Only if no photo (see 2D-5) |

**Important:** `initialData` (from "Edit profile" flow) takes priority. ENS pre-fill only applies to new profiles.

**Acceptance:** New wallet user sees ENS data in onboarding fields. Editing profile doesn't overwrite with ENS data.

